OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778328667
OL,3,CSouthampton charged with spying by EFL
OL,4,Cahead of play-off against Middlesbrough
OL,6,FThe incident had revived memories of
OL,7,Fan incident when the league issued a
OL,8,Ffine of #200,000 to Leeds for spying
OL,9,Fon a Derby training session before a
OL,10,Fmatch between the two clubs in January
OL,11,F2019.
OL,13,FBoth Middlesbrough and Southampton FC
OL,14,Fhave been approached for comment.
OL,16,FAn EFL statement on Friday night (8
OL,17,FMay) read: "Southampton Football Club
OL,18,Fhas today been charged with a breach
OL,19,Fof EFL Regulations, and the matter
OL,20,Fwill be referred to an Independent
OL,21,FDisciplinary Commission.
OL,26,@yD@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778328667
OL,3,CSouthampton charged with spying by EFL
OL,4,Cahead of play-off against Middlesbrough
OL,6,F"This follows a request from the EFL
OL,7,Ffor the club's observations after a
OL,8,Fcomplaint from Middlesbrough relating
OL,9,Fto alleged unauthorised filming on
OL,10,Fprivate property ahead of the two
OL,11,Fclubs meeting in Saturday's Sky Bet
OL,12,FChampionship play-off semi-final first
OL,13,Fleg.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778328667
OL,3,CSouthampton charged with spying by EFL
OL,4,Cahead of play-off against Middlesbrough
OL,6,F"The charges relate to the following
OL,7,FRegulations: EFL Regulation 3.4, which
OL,8,Frequires clubs to act towards each
OL,9,Fother with the utmost good faith; and
OL,10,FEFL Regulation 127, which prohibits
OL,11,Fany club from observing, or attempting
OL,12,Fto observe, another club's training
OL,13,Fsession within 72 hours of a scheduled
OL,14,Fmatch between the two clubs.
OL,16,F"Under EFL Regulations, Southampton
OL,17,Fwould ordinarily have 14 days to
OL,18,Frespond to the charges.
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778328667
OL,3,CSouthampton charged with spying by EFL
OL,4,Cahead of play-off against Middlesbrough
OL,6,F"However, given the nature of the
OL,7,Fmatter, the EFL will ask the
OL,8,FIndependent Disciplinary Commission to
OL,9,Fshorten the response period and to
OL,10,Flist a hearing at the earliest
OL,11,Fopportunity.
OL,13,F"The league will make no further
OL,14,Fcomment whilst proceedings are
OL,15,Fongoing."
OL,17,FSaints responded to the EFL charge,
OL,18,Fsaying: "Southampton Football Club
OL,19,Facknowledges the statement issued by
OL,20,Fthe EFL in relation to alleged
OL,21,Fbreaches of EFL Regulations.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUwD@IO]zD@IOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778328667
OL,3,CSouthampton charged with spying by EFL
OL,4,Cahead of play-off against Middlesbrough
OL,6,F"We can confirm that we will be fully
OL,7,Fcooperating with the League throughout
OL,8,Fthis process.
OL,10,F"Given the ongoing nature of the
OL,11,Fmatter, the club is unable to comment
OL,12,Fany further at this time."
OL,14,FMiddlesbrough say they will not be
OL,15,Fcommenting at this time.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUtD@ZO]
